obfuscation: I forget nothing , haughty lady .
original: I forget nothing, haughty lady.

obfuscation: I love you desperately , my life is in your hand -- I lay it at your feet !
original:
I love you desperately,
  my life is in your hand--I lay it at your feet!

obfuscation: Give me hope , and what I lack in education and polite accomplishments , that I will endeavour to acquire .
original:
Give me hope, and what I
  lack in education and polite accomplishments, that I will endeavour to
  acquire.

obfuscation: Drive me to despair , and in death alone I shall look for consolation .
original:
Drive me to despair, and in death alone I shall look for
  consolation.

obfuscation: I am proud and can not stoop to implore .
original: I am proud and cannot stoop to implore.

obfuscation: I have spoken and I wait your word .
original:
I have spoken and I wait
  your word.

obfuscation: You shall not wait long .
original: You shall not wait long.

obfuscation: Your proffered love I haughtily reject .
original: Your proffered love I haughtily reject.

obfuscation: Go , sir , and learn to cast your eyes on some village maiden in your own poor rank -- they should be lowered before your captain 's daughter .
original:
Go, sir, and learn to cast your eyes on some village maiden in
  your own poor rank--they should be lowered before your captain's daughter.

obfuscation: Refrain , audacious tar , Your suit from pressing , Remember what you are , And whom covering !
original:
Refrain, audacious tar,
                        Your suit from pressing,
                      Remember what you are,
                        And whom addressing!

obfuscation: I 'd laugh my rank to scorn In union holy , Were he more highly born Or I more lowly !
original:
I'd laugh my rank to scorn
                        In union holy,
                      Were he more highly born
                        Or I more lowly!

obfuscation: Proud lady , have your way , Unfeeling beauty !
original:
Proud lady, have your way,
                        Unfeeling beauty!

obfuscation: You speak and I obey , It is my duty !
original:
You speak and I obey,
                        It is my duty!

obfuscation: I am the lowliest tar That sails the water , And you , proud maiden , are My captain 's daughter !
original:
I am the lowliest tar
                        That sails the water,
                      And you, proud maiden, are
                        My captain's daughter!

obfuscation: My heart with anguish torn Bows down before her , She laughs my love to scorn , Yet I adore her !
original:
My heart with anguish torn
                        Bows down before her,
                      She laughs my love to scorn,
                        Yet I adore her!

obfuscation: Can I survive this overbearing Or live a life of mad despairing , My proffered love despised , rejected ?
original:
Can I survive this overbearing
                        Or live a life of mad despairing,
                        My proffered love despised, rejected?

original: No, no, it's not to be expected!
